{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart@navapbc.com","data":{"compacted_at":1784346157828838001,"compiled_state":{"alias":"pristine-horrible-whapuku","assignee":"","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"d0f2d81a9e7b2cf3901dd7b7bc598d03f9d2d596","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","material: a467d66dc32d5003","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 4","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (d0f2d81a9)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:f106967692feba1418ed8a1c9ec295dae8d9dd3f","dep 3df23a46724ebf2f375e353938db5da78a6f2936d24ab73bc3aa6803734cfbad .github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml","dep eb3f516eb366a40b5a2404eb2e8ab1af5bc1154a795d7b0defddc3c0b08eb387 docs/identity-setup.md","dep af8b6e453a51d0fbc994f00b37900cad4096d60fe215c793e791d522bc39dd90 rebar.toml","dep 9a229c6a1b259a9d6f8f0c59b1f8949ac4e56c26c7fbaf1027202244ad046fc6 src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py","dep 506332bfe57d303af0934f7f83f3e4296d16c1b0b750003871a48b7569831ddf src/rebar/_config_schema.py"],"material_fingerprint":"a467d66dc32d5003","merged_log_commit":"f106967692feba1418ed8a1c9ec295dae8d9dd3f","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784231031906440000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":2,"unsigned":14},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"2d5545c1578207798d0fd05e963845dadf64ca3dd9fa52ea0bf627d36cdb357e","event_uuid":"601f405b-7c2e-4812-81dc-1f3c925f1370","position":{"commit_sha":"881f800f4d6d60b1d04900dc2dee60d8160432d3","position":"1784233909175604355-601f405b-7c2e-4812-81dc-1f3c925f1370"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"4dae51aba48c2a955c30a33c4730557ffadd7ebffc2e78b0c8df98ad96e3e582","event_uuid":"75e6db15-f6b6-4e23-9aa6-b1800c02ee35","position":{"commit_sha":"3af5cf575c71b10b9f475bce42e2a97301476484","position":"1784262492431096001-75e6db15-f6b6-4e23-9aa6-b1800c02ee35"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"22d157b1109a60c724d04c726269867c9e41046814f2bbcb410d8231244c2e8b","event_uuid":"e4059709-c4c6-494a-8570-6e64069dca44","position":{"commit_sha":"bd8e133ca3e22cdaf2d35b1c179ec87e160919f2","position":"1784262494960158001-e4059709-c4c6-494a-8570-6e64069dca44"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e533bbc2-be02-4c77-890b-73fde9abf109","comments":[],"created_at":1784225578229270001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"0fa7fe8f-510c-472e-9727-0a76d4af9831","relation":"supersedes","target_id":"a422-a27e-44e4-4697"},{"link_uuid":"0690c8fd-2ec8-43ee-9d67-c8589656c34c","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88"},{"link_uuid":"82456647-1a53-40f3-8473-171142aec432","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"27ae-8322-9278-4a7c"},{"link_uuid":"8f5618fa-61a3-4442-96b4-b007c5b300ef","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"f735-9095-ea47-40f4"}],"description":"## Context\n\nrebar's authenticated-authorship capability is fully built and merged (identity epic\ngnu-whale-ichor / e68d, foundation 2fd4, op-cert asymmetric 6d0d), and the HMAC->sshsig\nattestation migration completed cleanly on 2026-07-14. But the LAST MILE — turning on\nevent-authorship signing so `identity.require_authenticated` can be flipped to `true` —\nwas deferred out of every build epic into the parked idea a422 (dated-circular-velvetworm)\nand never executed. Post-mortem findings this epic remediates:\n\n- **Local sessions/worktrees on this machine** have no persistent signing key (no\n  `identity.signing_key`, no `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`, no `.rebar/current_identity`);\n  only ~4 one-off validation-demo signed events exist store-wide vs ~5,000 unsigned.\n- **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml`) already has the full\n  key-materialize + job-level env wiring (story 9e76/cc0b) but is secret-gated: with\n  `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` unset it writes UNSIGNED (advisory). Exactly one CI-authored\n  signed event exists store-wide.\n- **Gerrit-side operations** (review-bot signing 245e, reconciler inline-sign 9e76,\n  opcert-service) landed in code, but the post-deploy validation canary 1787 was\n  FORCE-CLOSED \"pending post-deploy run\" — never confirmed to sign on the deployed VM.\n- **The guardrail** bug 27ae made the merge-gate config-driven and set an `enforce_since`\n  grandfather boundary; the perf blocker 1cc0 is fixed. Flipping the flag today would fail\n  every push because the store is unsigned — the flip must land AFTER every writer signs,\n  in the same change that pins `enforce_since`.\n\nThis epic supersedes a422 and drives the rollout to the point where\n`identity.require_authenticated = true` can be enabled with NOTHING failing on any writer\nsurface.\n\n## Scope / planned child stories\n\n1. **Local machine signing** — provision a persistent signing key for local\n   worktrees/sessions (per-machine `identity.signing_key` or exported\n   `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`), register/confirm the identity, verify steady-state\n   signed events across a fresh session.\n2. **GitHub Actions signing** — populate the `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` secret and confirm\n   `reconcile-bridge` (and its canary) produce signed events on a real run.\n3. **Gerrit-side signing** — finish canary 1787: confirm the deployed review-bot /\n   reconciler / opcert-service signs its ticket writes on the VM.\n4. **Grandfathering remediation** — verify/repin `identity.enforce_since` to the\n   flip-cutover commit and confirm `verify-identity` grandfathers all pre-boundary events;\n   add/confirm a regression test around the boundary.\n5. **The atomic flip** — set `identity.require_authenticated = true` + the pinned\n   `enforce_since` in ONE change; confirm the merge-gate enforces going forward.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every writer environment (this machine, GitHub Actions, Gerrit-side services)\n      produces SIGNED events in steady state, confirmed by `rebar verify-identity`\n      reporting them `verified`.\n- [ ] The rollout is sequenced safely: signing is confirmed on every surface BEFORE the\n      enforcement flag is flipped (so the gate never goes red on an unsigned writer).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **With `identity.require_authenticated = true`, no writer surface fails.** Each of\n      (a) a fresh local session/worktree on this machine, (b) a GitHub Actions run that writes\n      tickets (`reconcile-bridge`), and (c) the Gerrit side is proven safe under enforcement:\n      local and CI each produce a signed, `verified` event; the Gerrit side **either** produces\n      a signed `verified` event from an in-scope writer **or** is proven (with file/line\n      evidence, per the Gerrit-side story) to have no in-scope writer — only non-writing\n      (`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`, e.g. opcert-service) and gate-exempt (`code_review`, e.g. the\n      review-bot) operations. `rebar verify-identity` exits 0 in every case; no CI job goes red\n      and no write is rejected. Proof: `authorship: {signed: >=1}` + a `verified` verdict for\n      each in-scope writer, plus the recorded classification for any surface with none.\n- [ ] **Pre-flip events are grandfathered.** `identity.enforce_since` is pinned to the\n      enforcement-cutover commit; `rebar verify-identity` over the full history exits 0 with\n      zero pre-boundary events flagged. Proof: a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the\n      boundary passes the gate, while a new unsigned/forged in-scope event AFTER the boundary\n      FAILS it.\n- [ ] **Signing is provisioned everywhere before the flip.** Every surface that has an\n      in-scope writer has a persistent signing key configured (local per-machine key,\n      populated `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY` CI secret, and a Gerrit-side service key iff the\n      Gerrit-side story finds an in-scope writer) and has produced at least one steady-state\n      signed event confirmed via `rebar verify-identity` — done and confirmed BEFORE\n      `require_authenticated` is set true.\n- [ ] **The flip is atomic and enforcing.** `identity.require_authenticated = true` and the\n      pinned `enforce_since` land in a single change; after it, `verify-identity`\n      demonstrably FAILS on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event (enforcement is real, not\n      advisory).\n- [ ] **End-state:** the epic's five child stories are all in status `closed`, and each of\n      their changes is present on `origin/main` (verifiable via `rebar show` per child +\n      `git log origin/main`).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"rebar.toml","reason":"flip [identity] require_authenticated + pin enforce_since (grandfathering + atomic-flip stories)"},{"path":".github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml","reason":"CI signing: REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY materialize + job-level env wiring the GitHub Actions story validates"},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py","reason":"enforce_since grandfathering check remediated + regression-tested"},{"path":"src/rebar/_config_schema.py","reason":"identity.enforce_since / require_authenticated config keys"},{"path":"docs/identity-setup.md","reason":"rollout runbook updated for all three writer surfaces"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","27ae-8322-9278-4a7c"],["relates_to","8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88"],["relates_to","f735-9095-ea47-40f4"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"e4059709-c4c6-494a-8570-6e64069dca44","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","ticket_type":"epic","title":"Complete authenticated-identity rollout: make identity.require_authenticated safe to enable across all writers","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["4ecf33bd-6533-425c-a642-6b00dc6ee2fd","0fa7fe8f-510c-472e-9727-0a76d4af9831","0690c8fd-2ec8-43ee-9d67-c8589656c34c","82456647-1a53-40f3-8473-171142aec432","1ffa28b9-568d-4271-93d9-6374912166f1","1cdef6b1-3749-4629-84df-1078d0d79311","857b69d8-49f8-452e-9d20-c7d53573c298","e989a14e-fbe2-43f8-a35c-e2980effcbc3","fce8e26b-bad1-4eb8-aedb-e6e208e6c22d","99a96e93-d66c-4461-b889-6ca3b2a5150b","1afd4bbc-0f6f-4bad-a91d-3629579de23e","f07b3efe-28eb-4f2a-8949-a8ed75f5e392","32303925-865e-4a89-b2cf-7f780cd46587","aad6549b-6fa2-4177-9237-62e874d9fbfe","311c93eb-b339-4dd0-bdf7-25bb842b962d","09880924-065c-4a88-96b8-09024e3200c5","8f5618fa-61a3-4442-96b4-b007c5b300ef","9f493b61-ea11-4d2e-bfcd-1bd420abf65b","827d2445-d569-44de-8f0e-b27265f2a157","601f405b-7c2e-4812-81dc-1f3c925f1370","14cf1670-ed99-44a7-8394-f5882eedce21","ffb329fe-c269-4a8d-a64e-f615a8bed377","75e6db15-f6b6-4e23-9aa6-b1800c02ee35","e4059709-c4c6-494a-8570-6e64069dca44"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784346157828838001,"uuid":"4fff5146-c3ff-46fe-980d-12a7e016ff8f"}